Eiichi, creator of the first "carrot box" passed 10 years ago. This modern interpretation, though similar in shape and function, pales greatly to the works of not just Eichii, but artists like "Big Man" Kiyoshi and Tsukiko "Melon Queen" Takahashi. 

As the 80s came and went, Kiyoshi would see his works seized by the billion dollar empire YUTANI, igniting the rise of ruthless corporate manufacturing and the eventual downfall of box artistry. What you see now is a soulless product of capitalism, a ghost of what used to be.
